caption.text:
Since I was born I've been blessed with a greatest man in the world. He is someone that always supports me wherever I go, helps me to stand back when I'm falling, wipes away my tears when I'm crying, tells me the right way when I did something wrong, lends me his jacket when it's raining outside, comforts me when I didn't feel well. 
Unfortunately, he passed away not to long ago. Now that he's gone, I feel something is missing inside me. I feel like my heart is being ripped apart, knowing that a man that I loved most is gone. Forever. 
If only I had a second chance, I don't care if it means I had to give up all of me. I just want to meet him again, feeling his warm hug, hearing him said "I'm proud of you" once again, waiting for him to come home from work again. 
I miss you dad, I miss you so much that it hurts. I can't accept the fact that you're no longer here, that you can't attend my graduation, walk me down the aisle on my wedding or watch my children grows up.

I know, you've been suffering too long. All the tears and anger you hold back for me. For us. I'm sorry I can't be the one to heal your wounds. I hope you have a better life up there in heaven. I love you dad. May peace be upon you.

31/1/2016
